  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "On Snapchat, the concept of \"followers\" is different from some other social media platforms. Instead of followers, Snapchat uses a concept of \"friends,\" meaning users who have added each other. You can see who you're friends with by going to your Friends list on the app. Here's how you can get an idea of who might be following you:\n\n1. **Check Your Friends List**: To see who you have added back, go to your profile and tap on \"My Friends.\" This will show you a list of people you are friends with on Snapchat.\n\n2. **Added Me Section**: To see who has added you but you haven't added back, go to the section called \"Added Me.\" This will show users who have added you but are not yet in your Friends list.\n\n3. **Stories Views**: When you post a story, you can see who has viewed it. This can give you an idea of who is actively engaging with your content.\n\n4. **Privacy Settings**: If your settings allow others to send you snaps and view your stories, users who are not on your Friends list can view them, depending on your privacy settings. Go to your profile, tap on the gear icon to access settings, and select \"Who Can...\" to adjust who can contact you and view your story.\n\n5. **Snap Map**: If you have Snap Map enabled and have set it to share with certain friends, you can see who these friends are by tapping the settings (gear icon) on the Snap Map and reviewing who you've shared your location with.\n\nRemember that anyone on Snapchat can add you and follow your public content, but if you haven't added them back, you won't have a mutual friendship on the app. Always review your privacy settings to control who can see your content.",
